# Route Registration Checklist

Every new route in this app requires updates in the router, header config, and desktop/mobile navigation. Missing one causes a broken header title, missing nav link, or invisible page.

## Current Routes

- Primary app routes: `/dashboard`, `/accounts`, `/budget`, `/transactions`, `/setup`, `/preferences`, `/profile`, `/household`, `/formulas`, `/more`.
- Redirects: `/` -> `/dashboard`, `/cashflow` -> `/dashboard`, `/settings` -> `/preferences`.
- Public routes: `/welcome`, `/login`, `/register`.

## Required Places

| File | What to add |
|------|-------------|
| `App.tsx` | Lazy import and `<Route path="..." element={...} />` inside the protected `Layout` |
| `Layout.tsx` `routeConfig` | `'/path': { title: 'Page Title', icon: IconComponent }` |
| `Sidebar.tsx` `navigationItems` | `{ name: '...', href: '/path', icon: IconComponent }` |
| `BottomTabBar.tsx` or `More.tsx` | Tab entry or `<MenuRow>` link for mobile nav |

`/household` is conditional in `Sidebar.tsx` through `useHousehold().isInHousehold`; preserve that behavior for household-only navigation.

## Example

Adding a new `/goals` page:

```tsx
// App.tsx
const Goals = lazy(() => import('./pages/Goals').then(m => ({ default: m.Goals })));
<Route path="goals" element={<Suspense fallback={null}><Goals /></Suspense>} />

// Layout.tsx routeConfig
'/goals': { title: 'Goals', icon: Target },

// Sidebar.tsx navigationItems
{ name: 'Goals', href: '/goals', icon: Target }

// More.tsx (mobile) or BottomTabBar.tsx
<MenuRow href="/goals" icon={Target} label="Goals" />
```

## Rule

When adding or renaming a route, update every relevant location before finishing. The `routeConfig` in `Layout.tsx` drives the page header; if it is missing, the header silently falls back to "Dashboard".
